The paper deals with distributed algorithms and graph theory, which are topics that are commonly found in the sub-categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Graph Theory (cs.GT), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the problem of finding a minimum vertex cover on bipartite graphs, which is a problem related to graph theory and computational complexity. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
